* :ZgEnq18ZIZDmBf85: "There is also another interpretation. It rests on a not necessarily linguistic or symbolic conception of semantics. This third approach, of Gestalt derivation (Albertazzi, 2013), explains associations in terms of patterns of qualitative similarity present in different sensory modalities and perceived as such: for example, hot and cold, sad and happy, and pleasant and unpleasant, are connotative properties of both sounds and colors."
